    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pail-like or cone-shaped vessels, often having handles, made of bronze, silver, ceramic, glass, or another material. They were often decorated; used in the Iron Age, ancient Egypt, Asia, in the ancient Roman world, and in Christian religious rituals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
